Spec: Agent Skills Service
Purpose:
  Download, verify, and deploy SpecDD Agent Skills releases into Agent Skills directories.

Structure:
  ./agentskills.ts: Agent Skills deployment service implementation.
  ./agentskills.test.ts: Agent Skills deployment service tests.

Owns:
  ./agentskills.ts
  ./agentskills.test.ts

References:
  ../../infrastructure/fetch-client.sdd
  ../../infrastructure/file-system.sdd
  ../../infrastructure/temp-directory.sdd
  ../logger/service.sdd
  ../signature-verifier/service.sdd

Must:
  Accept @Logger, @FetchClient, @FileSystem, @TempDirectory, and @SignatureVerifier through constructor parameters.
  Expose @AgentSkills.deploy for the agentskills deploy command flow.
  Accept an explicit release version or latest.
  Use GitHub repository specdd/agentskills for release lookup.
  Treat explicit release versions as GitHub release tags.
  Resolve latest to the current GitHub latest release before downloading assets.
  Download the agentskills.zip asset to a unique temporary folder.
  Download the agentskills.zip.asc asset to the same temporary folder.
  Verify agentskills.zip against agentskills.zip.asc before applying files.
  Apply no Agent Skills files when signature verification fails.
  Install into .agents/skills under the target root directory.
  Support release zip entries rooted at .agents/skills/specdd-*.
  Support release zip entries rooted at specdd-*.
  Install only skill directories whose basename starts with specdd- and that contain SKILL.md.
  Ignore release entries for non-specdd-prefixed skills.
  Create parent directories needed for files that are written.
  Write missing files under specdd-* skill directories.
  Overwrite existing files under specdd-* skill directories.
  Preserve all target skill directories whose basename does not start with specdd-.
  Return resolved release version, install directory path, signer fingerprint, installed skill names, written paths, overwritten paths, and ignored release paths.
  Log release resolution, successful asset downloads, signature verification outcome, ignored release entries, written files, overwritten files, and deployment completion.

Must not:
  Write downloaded release files outside a temporary folder.
  Apply files before signature verification succeeds.
  Delete target files or directories.
  Write files outside the .agents/skills install directory.
  Write, overwrite, delete, or prune any target skill directory whose basename does not start with specdd-.
  Execute unzip, gpg, or any other external command.

Depends on:
  @CliError
  @Logger
  @FetchClient
  @FileSystem
  @TempDirectory
  @SignatureVerifier
  GitHub releases
  jszip
  Node.js path handling

Exposes:
  @AgentSkills
  @AgentSkills.deploy

Accepts:
  @AgentSkillsDeployRequest

Returns:
  @AgentSkillsDeployResult

Raises:
  @AgentSkillsReleaseNotFoundError
  @AgentSkillsAssetNotFoundError
  @AgentSkillsDownloadError
  @AgentSkillsFilesystemError
  @AgentSkillsZipReadError
  @AgentSkillsUnsafeEntryPathError
  @AgentSkillsNoInstallableSkillsError
  @AgentSkillsTargetWriteError

Handles:
  latest release request
  explicit release version request
  missing agentskills.zip release asset
  missing agentskills.zip.asc release asset
  failed asset download
  signature verification failure
  empty or populated target Agent Skills directory
  release entries rooted at .agents/skills
  release entries rooted at top-level skill directories
  non-specdd-prefixed release entries
  specdd-prefixed release entries without SKILL.md
  unsafe zip file entry path
